[28.988, "o", "\r\n\u001b[38;2;142;68;207m\u001b[1m  в”Ғв”Ғ CLAUDE SYNTHESIS в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    # BRCA1 (ENSG00000012048) вҖ” Expert Analysis\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    **Function and molecular role.** BRCA1 encodes a 1,863 aa RING-domain E3 ubiquitin ligase that operates as the scaffold of multiple DNA damage response complexes (BRCA1-A, -B, -C, and the BRCA1вҖ“PALB2вҖ“BRCA2 axis). It is the central licensing factor for homologous recombination (HR) repair of DNA double-strand breaks: it antagonizes 53BP1/RIF1/Shieldin to permit end resection, recruits CtIP and the MRN complex, and ultimately enables RAD51 filament loading via PALB2вҖ“BRCA2. Beyond HR, BRCA1 governs S/G2 checkpoint enforcement, replication fork protection, transcription-coupled repair, and X-chromosome inactivation through its BRCT-mediated phospho-peptide recognition.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    **Transcript and isoform complexity.** The 47 annotated transcripts (33 protein-coding) across the ~126 kb locus are functionally non-trivial. The canonical full-length BRCA1-p220 is the HR-competent species, but О”11q (which skips most of exon 11) is constitutively expressed and confers partial PARP inhibitor resistance by retaining BRCT function while losing the central DNA-binding region. Splice-altering variants вҖ” particularly those affecting the exon 10/11 boundary, the canonical donor of exon 22, and the BRCT linker вҖ” are a major source of misclassified VUS. Any variant interpretation pipeline that ignores isoform-level effects will systematically misclassify clinically actionable alleles.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    **Key variants and disease associations.** Germline loss-of-function alleles confer ~65вҖ“72% lifetime breast cancer risk and ~39вҖ“44% ovarian cancer risk, with elevated risk for pancreatic, prostate (aggressive), and fallopian tube carcinomas. The Ashkenazi founder alleles c.68_69delAG (185delAG) and c.5266dupC (5382insC) remain the highest-yield screening targets in that population. RING-domain missense variants (e.g., C61G) abolish E3 ligase activity and BARD1 heterodimerization; BRCT missense variants (e.g., M1775R, A1708E) disrupt phospho-peptide binding and are HR-deficient by saturation genome editing (Findlay et al.) and homology-directed repair functional assays. Biallelic BRCA1 loss causes Fanconi anemia complementation group S (FANCS). Somatically, BRCA1 promoter hypermethylation phenocopies mutation in ~10вҖ“15% of high-grade serous ovarian carcinoma and is equally predictive of platinum and PARPi response.\r\n    **Clinical and therapeutic implications.** BRCA1-deficient tumors are synthetic-l"]
[0.000, "o", "ethal with PARP inhibition (olaparib, rucaparib, niraparib, talazoparib are all FDA-approved across breast, ovarian, pancreatic, and prostate indications), and show enhanced sensitivity to platinum agents and topoisomerase I inhibitors. Resistance arises predictably via secondary reversion mutations restoring the reading frame, 53BP1/REV7/Shieldin loss, or replication fork stabilization вҖ” all detectable in ctDNA and worth monitoring longitudinally. HRD genomic scar scores (LOH, TAI, LST; Myriad myChoice and FoundationOne CDx) remain the clinically validated functional readouts.\r\n    **Experimental recommendations.** For variant characterization, deploy saturation genome editing in HAP1 or hESCs (the Findlay framework remains the gold standard for SNV-level functional scoring across the BRCT and RING domains) coupled with a DR-GFP or traffic-light reporter HR assay in BRCA1-null U2OS or RPE1 cells. For tumor profiling, pair whole-exome/genome sequencing with HRD scar quantification and RNA-seq for splice-iso"]
[0.000, "o", "form calling вҖ” the latter is non-negotiable given the exon 11 skipping biology. For resistance mechanism work, use long-read sequencing (PacBio/ONT) on ctDNA to resolve secondary reversion events that short-read panels miss, and CRISPR screens against the 53BP1вҖ“Shieldin axis to map the resistance landscape. Finally, any preclinical model should be validated by RAD51 foci formation after ionizing radiation вҖ” the single most direct functional readout of HR competence.\r\n"]
